history.content:
Dear EECS Student,

The Computing Research Association (CRA) is interested in career development among students in computing fields. They would like to hear about your experiences as a student, as well as your plans for the future. To that end, I encourage you to complete their brief survey, which will take no more than 25 minutes to complete.  It is very important for us to get a good number of responses so we can see how UC Berkeley compares with other institutions. 

Should you decide to complete the survey, you will be entered into a raffle for a $100 gift card to Amazon!

Please click the link below to take the survey:

Take the survey.

Or copy and paste the URL below into your internet browser:

https://crasurvey.co1.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_8CAClu1Qg8yscwl

 
The survey is being conducted by the CRA’s Center for Evaluating the Research Pipeline (CERP). For more information on CERP, please visit their website: http://cra.org/cerp/.

Deadline is December 12th! 

Many thanks in advance!
history.subject: Take the Computing Research Association Survey
